<p>Canadian models will feature a 3.2L V6 engine mated to a six-speed automatic transmission with, of course, Audi?s Quattro all-wheel drive system as standard equipment.  </p>

<p>Measurements show that the Q5 will definitely be a large <span class="caps">SUV </span>- with 4,663 mm in length, 1,880 mm in width and a 2,810 mm long wheelbase.  The size of the Q5 is slightly larger than one of its closest competitors the <span class="caps">BMW X3.</span></p>

<p>The Q5 will be the first Audi to use the automakers third-generation Multi Media Interface system and it will also be available with side assist blind spot sensors, a stability control system that adapts its responses to the surface being driven on and whether cargo is being carried on the roof as well as front and rear parking sensors with a rearview camera.</p>
